suffered which greatly impacted my trading This seeped into my trading life I began trade emotionally 2 I was mainly relying technical analysis instead using conjunction fundamental analysis 3 I was trading companies I didn t understand 4 I was trading companies didn t real value would unattractive long term buys if I were actually invest them 5 I strayed my trading indicators I normally used worked during my internet monies trading era I was using way too many There was way too much noise charts I killed my account essentially gave up long time I dealt other personal problems my life I focused structure instead using indicators better my trading became 2 I only traded companies I would comfortable investing 3 I look good companies getting attacked media I wait them go discount use my indicators able see when recovery starting form sellers become exhausted 4 I stopped smoking or drinking 5 I stopped trading after hours 6 I leave runners once I m profit majority my position 7 I range I d rather make my money going long then rotate into another beaten down 8 I stick my set rules 9 I reflect every trade what emotions was I dealing What reasons did I enter trade What we re some unnecessary risks I took can avoided next trade How could I exited trade better 10 I learned how use options 11 I stopped marrying stocks my head By I mean I stopped becoming emotionally attached companies I became purely methodical my trades If re wondering what indicators I use s 2 different EMAs different lengths depending chart Keltner channels I like them better than bollinger bands I one more script I use but It s personal use only sorry If I gave away would worthless Not sale My ending advice focus structure volume You can come back massive failures One step time Keep learning don t trade more than few percentages your portfolio time The only book I recommend A complete guide volume price analysis by Anna Coulling It s not newest book but s information great Got couple bucks kindle I will update my trading journey continues further along I genuinely thought I would never see my account return these levels but these last few months been great learning period Peace out

Fiat persists due cheap pernicious illusion I m not most concise or poetic storyteller but I think there s something important When we were young my friend described her dream life She wanted live large 5 bedroom house small village not too far major city huge garden her kids dogs play She grew up poor neighbourhood Her family never had any money She learnt how make ends meet tight budget She excelled school She went university She got degree sensible practical desirable subject She got job which pays considerably more than average She met man who now her husband his job also pays more than average A decade ago they bought small house together The house cost 180k It doubled value now They ve both been saving diligently too making sacrifices wherever possible whilst also raising children They ve amassed 100k savings Both them did everything right Or least everything they were supposed do A decade ago my considerably older cousin bought 5 bedroom house beautiful village 750k an interest only mortgage sole earner family 5 Having heard all intricate details my friend s dream house I can assure precisely Two weeks ago my cousin retired early put his house up sale 1 5M Meanwhile my friend super happy She paid down fair amount her mortgage she her husband saved earnestly she s received STUNNING bonus 180k rising value her property Many people she grew up did not buy house young nor did they save so carefully She did everything right She s winning She really feels like she winning She winning right She doesn t study UK housing particularly closely If she did she d see her dream home actually further out reach now than was decade ago Despite every late night work every holiday she did not go every piece furniture she rejuvenated Freecycle all savings sacrifices her dream home less obtainable her than was 10 years ago Here we arrive point Or rather disgracefully inelegant metaphor which I hope will demonstrate point The fiat world essentially rubber ladder clamp somewhere near bottom approx 20 way up Once clamp place fiat gods grip very top rung ladder then stretch eternally upwards 80 rungs get elevated upwards 80 rungs feel like they re winning 70 rungs so fricking happy about how amazingly quickly they re getting elevated they don t realise rung above them rapidly rising faster further away them This grand ruse money printer The money printer makes people nominally richer actually poorer simultaneously For lower rungs ladder above clamp creates illusion they re winning when they re actually losing I realise UK centric story but I ve had peek net wealth per household s broadly same story across entire western world Those highest rungs ladder engorging themselves wealth they never truly earnt They no reason complain nor produce anything worthwhile but s different story when their wealth effortlessly growing so rapidly Those lower rungs ladder above clamp happy sustain because they think they re winning too One day my friend will realise despite every effort imaginable her dream truly dead She will become disillusioned She will start questioning everything For now she happy we still early
